<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta content='text/html; charset=UTF-8' http-equiv='Content-Type' />

  <style>
    * {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', 'PingFang SC', 'Hiragino Sans GB', 'Microsoft YaHei', 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol';
      font-weight: 300;
      box-sizing: border-box;
      color: #46454c;
    }

    .header {
      background-color: #71a4ea;
      padding: .8rem 2rem;
    }

    .email-container {
      max-width: 900px;
      background-color: #fbfbfb;
      margin: auto;
      box-shadow: 0px 5px 5px 2px #46454c45;
    }

    .email-body-container {
      padding: 2rem;
    }

    .big {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      color: #fbfbfb;
    }

    b {
      font-weight: 400;
    }

    a {
      color: #71a4ea;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    hr {
      margin: 2rem 0;
      opacity: .5;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="email-container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1>You have been granted access to Brittle Pins</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="email-body-container">
      <p>
        You requested access to <b>Brittle Pins</b> for the email address <b><%= @email %></b>.
      </p>

      <p>
        Now you can <a href="https://brittle-pins.com/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">sign up</a>
        using your invitation code: <span class="big"><%= @invitation_code %></span>
      </p>

      <p>
        Please note that the code is only valid for the email that was specified when sending the request.
        It should be used before <b><%= @expires_at %></b>. After this date, you will have to request a new code.
      </p>

      <p>If you did not request an invitation, please ignore this message.</p>

      <hr />

      <small>
        Please don't reply directly to this email.
        Instead, you can <a href="mailto:admin@brittle-pins.com?subject=Access granted">contact our admin</a>.
      </small>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
